OL,3,CWoman, 31, left in hospital corridor
OL,4,Cfor hours at 'most vulnerable' `
OL,5,Cinquest
OL,7,FHer sister Miya Davis told an inquest
OL,8,Fat Horsham Coroner's Court that Ms
OL,9,FDavis, from Brighton, was "made to
OL,10,Ffend for herself" as she suffered from
OL,11,Fdiarrhoea and was coughing up blood
OL,12,Finto a small bowl.
OL,14,FArea coroner for West Sussex and
OL,15,FBrighton, Joanne Andrews, concluded Ms
OL,16,FDavis' death was from natural causes
OL,17,Fand that there was no evidence being
OL,18,Fplaced in the hospital corridor
OL,19,Fcontributed to her death.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/13
