OL,3,CWoman, 31, left in hospital corridor
OL,4,Cfor hours at 'most vulnerable' `
OL,5,Cinquest
OL,7,FMr Ifill said they were "left for
OL,8,Fhours" in the gangway and they kept
OL,9,Fasking what was happening.
OL,11,FDoctor Andrew Leonard, the consultant
OL,12,Fwho saw Ms Davis, told the court:
OL,13,F"Anyone being looked after in a
OL,14,Fcorridor is concerning as it's a
OL,15,Ffailure of normal care process."
OL,17,FDr Leonard told the inquest the
OL,18,Fpractice was becoming "increasingly
OL,19,Fthe norm" across the country in the
OL,20,Flast few years.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/13
