OL,5,Cinquest
OL,7,FThe senior nurse described how the
OL,8,Fcorridors are used every day and staff
OL,9,Fare allocated to work on the corridors
OL,10,Fwhere there is limited access to a
OL,11,Ftoilet, it is overcrowded and there is
OL,12,Fa lack of privacy for the patient.
OL,14,F"We would never move anyone to a
OL,15,Fcorridor out of choice," she said.
OL,16,F"Nobody should be nursed in the
OL,17,Fcorridor.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/13
